2003 Bench Press Nationals
Credit Card Instant Entry Form
This Contest is an Anabolic Steroid Free Meet
Qualifying

All Lifters MUST have lifted in a NASA Sanctioned Event since Feb. 1st, 2000 and placed 1st -3rd in that event. If NASA did not host an event in your state in 2001 you are Exempt from this Rule (See List).
Meet Director : Rich Peters, P.O. Box 735, Noble, OK. 73068   405-527-8513
Official Weigh-In Times
Early Weigh-In: 8:00 p.m.- 9:00 p.m. ( All Lifters )
Regular Weigh-In: 8:00 a.m.- 9:00 a.m. ( All Lifters )
Lifting Will Begin's At 10:00 a.m.

Rules: All NASA Rules will be strictly enforced. All Lifters will be required to have a current NASA Card. Membership Cards can be purchased at the meet for $25.00 per full year, High School are $15.00. All Lifters MUST wear a Lifting Singlet when competing. NASA Rulebook On-Line
Men's Weight Classes:
Women's Weight Classes:
Divisions for Bench Press Only for Men and Women
Pure - Never taken Any Anabolic Steroid.
Natural- Anabolic Steroid Free, minimum of 3 years.
Pure Novice: Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free, hasn't won Natural Nationals before 1996.
Teenage - 13 -19 years of age, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Juniors - 13 - 23 years of age, no Anabolic Steroids in Lifetime of lifter.
High School Pure - Any currently enrolled High School lifter, Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free.
Intermediate - Ages 24 - 29, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Sub Masters 1- Ages 30 - 34, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Sub Masters 2 -Ages 35 - 39, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Sub Masters Pure - Ages 30 - 39, no Anabolic Steroids in Lifetime of lifter.
Masters 1- Ages 40 - 49, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Masters 2 - Ages 50 - 59, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Masters 3 - Ages 60 - 69, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Masters 4 - Ages 70 +, no Anabolic Steroids for minimum of 3 years.
Masters (5) Pure - Ages 40+, Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free.
Awards In All Divisions and All Weight Classes
1st thru 5th will have their choice of several different styles of Beautiful Awards.
Awards will be presented for lifters placing 1st thru 5th in each Weight Class, in each Division
Return Entries and Fee's to:
Rich Peters, P.O. Box 735, Noble, OK. 73068   Phone # 405-527-8513
BP Only Entry Fee's Only : $50.00 for first division, $30.00 for all additional entries, per lifter.
Late Fee's
Add an Additional $10.00 per division entered if entry is made after Jan. 28th, 2002
Gold Card's MUST be sent with ALL Gold Card Entries! Gold Card Lates will $5.00 per Division
NO EXCEPTIONS - NO CHECKS ACCEPTED ON MEET DAY - CASH ONLY
Team Entry Fee's : $30.00 per Team Entered. Must be turned in with Team Roster by Saturday Morning before lifting begins. Awards for 1st thu 3rd for Men's and Women's Team.
